  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Women undergoing their first second or third cesarean section will be randomized into two
      groups. One group will have the abdominal bandage removed at 6 hours post-surgery and the
      other group will have the bandage removed at 24 hours. Staple removal will be at 5 - 7 days
      for both groups. The incision will be inspected at the time of staple removal. The 2 groups
      will be compared for incision disruption and infection. Also, the women will be asked about
      their satisfaction for time of bandage removal.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
